review_blob: Comrades standard Stout offering. One of my favorite styles the low ABV stout. This stout has a Heavy Dose of Coffee to set it apart from other standard stout offerings. Nice and smooth sweet chocolate coffee flavors.
As usual Hill Farmsteadreleased another great beer. Opened at roughly 1 year old. Still carbonated, funky and tart. Very balanced. A touch bready with a nice slightly dry finish.
beer_name: Hill Farmstead / Kissmeyer / Cambridge Nordic Saison

review_blob: One of the best stouts Ive had in a long time. Lucky enough to score a bottle from a local traveling to Colorado. Coffee Cinnamon Explosion. Really solid barrel profile, Thick and a touch roasty aided by the coffee. A very nice balanced stout. Cycle Has their stout game on point!

Casey has something really special going on up in the mountains. An awesome Hoppy funky beer. 

Aroma: Smells like: bread, barnyard, citrus, earthy

Appearance: Golden Haze, not super clear. 

Taste: Nice Bitterness with slight sour, the Description doesnt lie, Straight Pineapple Juice

Palate: Its a mediaum body feel with average carb with a slightly Bitter and long finish. 

Overall: One of my favorites from Casey. Cant complain at all.
